t-native-kqueue` would normally require an OS/architecture classifier such as `osx-x86_64`, which is not applicable to the Ubuntu runner and is not useful as generic test setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0458bda58a44923c016a3e65b7040c8193a8d4abf43deaef00\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 802, "output": 764, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32798, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782474155089, "responseId": "resp_0458bda58a44923c016a3e65ab8b10819396d9991ed9a482b4"}}
